{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","data":{"alias":"sopping-cloned-dragon","description":"## Why\n4b5b (change 581) documented the DELIVERED (diverged) design — raw-bytes authorship,\nHLC-epoch validity, the `{author_id, author_sig, epoch}` ledger, and a 4-way verdict\nwithout `key_not_valid_at_era`. Once TS1/TS2/TS3 transition the implementation to the\nAPPROVED design, the docs + ADR must be rewritten to match. Depends on TS1, TS2, TS3.\n(User rejected the delivered design; see session_log d7c0.)\n\n## What\nRewrite `docs/identity.md` and `docs/adr/0045-authenticated-identity.md` to the\napproved design:\n- Authorship = in-toto Statement (subject binds `{event_uuid, content_hash}`), DSSE\n  payloadType `application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json` (TS1).\n- Key validity = git-commit-ancestry over tickets-branch SHAs (`added_at_commit`,\n  `revoked_at_commit`), event valid iff its commit descends from added and not from\n  revoked (TS2) — and WHY the DAG (immutable) beats wall-clock/HLC ordering.\n- Snapshot ledger schema `{event_uuid, content_hash, signature, signer_pubkey,\n  position}` (TS3).\n- Verdict enum incl. `key_not_valid_at_era` + the verified/unverified/unsigned display\n  grouping (TS3).\n- Keep the docs-index linkage green.\n\n## Scope\nIn: docs/identity.md + ADR 0045 rewritten to the approved design; docs-index stays\ngreen. Out: the implementation (TS1/TS2/TS3).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `docs/identity.md` describes the in-toto Statement authorship, git-commit-ancestry\n  key validity, the approved ledger schema, and the verdict enum + grouping — matching\n  the delivered TS1/TS2/TS3 code (no HLC-epoch / raw-bytes / old-ledger language remains).\n- [ ] `docs/adr/0045-authenticated-identity.md` records the approved decisions\n  (in-toto Statement, opaque-id keying, git-commit-ancestry validity) with the DAG-vs-\n  wall-clock security rationale and rejected alternatives.\n- [ ] The docs-index completeness gate passes (`python scripts/check_docs_index.py\n  --check` exits 0).\n\n## file_impact\n- `docs/identity.md`\n- `docs/adr/0045-authenticated-identity.md`","id":"b134-7545-94fd-4746","parent_id":"e68d-b701-4dd9-47aa","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"transition: docs + ADR rewrite to approved design (in-toto, commit-ancestry, ledger, verdict)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783879637116271001,"uuid":"bf60066a-1e17-40db-9fe2-c5c32f65036c"}